e-court-begins-hearing-on-neet-exam-irregularities-6058876%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22America's%20plague%20of%20tyrannical%20homeowners%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Nosy%20neighbor%20with%20binoculars%20peeking%20over%20shrubs%2C%20shocked%20at%20neighbor's%20'NO%20HOA'%20sign%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F667ed9bb50b021b5caea7011%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWidespread%20HOA%20governance%20reinforces%20segregation%2C%20inflates%20housing%20costs%2C%20and%20makes%20everyone's%20life%20worse.%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3B%20Alyssa%20Powell%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESomeone%20picturing%20their%20local%20government%20might%20imagine%20a%20Norman%20Rockwell-esque%20portrait%20of%20a%20small-town%20mayor%20and%20a%20collection%20of%20other%20humble%20public%20servants.%20Or%20they%20might%20see%20a%20corrupt%20political%20machine%20governed%20by%20men%20in%20smoke-filled%20rooms.%20But%20no%20matter%20the%20form%20these%20local%20institutions%20take%20in%20one's%20mind%2C%20in%20most%20cases%2C%20people%20take%20%26quot%3Blocal%20government%26quot%3B%20to%20mean%20a%20public%20entity%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20it%20actually%20serves%20the%20public%20or%20not.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20not%20all%20local%20governments%20are%20public%20entities.%20Millions%20of%20Americans%20live%20in%20neighborhoods%20with%20their%20own%20forms%20of%20local%20representation%2C%20taxation%2C%20and%20public%20service%20provision.%20These%20private%20quasi-governments%20are%20called%20homeowner%20associations%2C%20or%20HOAs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20HOA-governed%20residential%20area%20may%20comprise%20just%20a%20few%20homes%2C%20or%20it%20may%20be%20a%20sprawling%20empire%20of%20thousands%20of%20households.%20Either%20way%2C%20anyone%20who%20buys%20property%20in%20HOA%20territory%20becomes%20a%20member%20of%20the%20association%2C%20with%20all%20the%20rights%20and%20responsibilities%20that%20implies.%20The%20benefits%20of%20HOA%20membership%20may%20include%20access%20to%20shared%20goods%20like%20trash%20collection%2C%20well-paved%20private%20roads%2C%20and%20landscaped%20common%20areas.%20Members%20may%20pay%20dues%20or%20be%20subject%20to%20strict%20regulations%20that%20limit%20their%20property%20rights.%20Even%20if%20the%20costs%20outweigh%20the%20benefits%2C%20HOA%20members%20tend%20to%20be%20stuck%20with%20them%20%E2%80%94%20unless%20they%20move%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENowhere%20are%20these%20miniature%20states%20more%20prevalent%20than%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fflorida-condo-owners-prices-drop-insurance-hoa-taxes-increase-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%20Florida%3C%2Fa%3E.%20While%20California%20has%20the%20most%20HOAs%20of%20any%20state%20(50%2C000)%2C%20Florida%20has%20far%20more%20HOA%20residents%20as%20a%20percentage%20of%20its%20population.%20A%20little%20over%20a%20third%20of%20Californians%20reside%20in%20an%20HOA-governed%20community%3B%20close%20to%2045%25%20of%20Floridians%20live%20under%20one%20of%20the%20state's%20estimated%2049%2C420%20HOAs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20new%20state%20law%2C%20signed%20by%20Gov.%20Ron%20DeSantis%20last%20month%2C%20is%20a%20long-overdue%20effort%20to%20protect%20individual%20property%20owners%20from%20the%20most%20power-mad%20of%20these%20quasi-governments.%20The%20law%20limits%20the%20extent%20to%20which%20HOAs%20can%20regulate%20and%20penalize%20decisions%20by%20individual%20households%3B%20as%20The%20Guardian%20put%20it%2C%20the%20law%20is%20about%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fus-news%2Farticle%2F2024%2Fjun%2F10%2Fflorida-homeowners-association-rule-changes%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecurbing%20the%20Karens%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%20HOAs%20will%20no%20longer%20be%20able%20to%20set%20draconian%20rules%20about%20parking%2C%20leaving%20garbage%20cans%20at%20the%20curb%2C%20or%20growing%20a%20vegetable%20garden%2C%20and%20the%20rules%20they%20do%20set%20will%20have%20to%20be%20more%20transparent.%20In%20addition%2C%20HOA%20board%20members%20will%20receive%20mandatory%20training.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bill's%20introduction%20was%20likely%20prompted%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbsnews.com%2Fmiami%2Fnews%2Fcurrent-former-members-of-hammocks-hoa-accused-in-2-million-theft-fraud%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20prominent%20embezzlement%20case%3C%2Fa%3E%20involving%20the%20board%20of%20one%20Florida%20HOA%2C%20but%20owners%20have%20long%20been%20frustrated%20with%20HOA%20rules.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20law's%20provisions%20are%20sensible%20reforms%20that%20more%20parts%20of%20the%20US%20should%20adopt.%20But%20they%20do%20little%20more%20than%20smooth%20out%20the%20rough%20edges%20in%20the%20HOA%20model%2C%20when%20the%20larger%20problem%20is%20the%20model%20itself.%20Widespread%20HOA%20governance%20reinforces%20segregation%2C%20inflates%20housing%20costs%2C%20and%20depletes%20the%20commons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20we%20want%20to%20rein%20in%20these%20private%20governments%2C%20end%20the%20housing%20crisis%2C%20and%20finish%20the%20job%20of%20racial%20integration%2C%20it%20will%20take%20more%20than%20some%20modest%20adjustments%20to%20HOA%20governance.%20We%20may%20need%20to%20break%20the%20system%20of%20privatized%20governance%20entirely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EHOAs%20sprang%20from%20the%20suburban%20boom%20of%20the%20late%201950s%20%E2%80%94%20the%20first%20association%20on%20record%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F26326906%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eformed%20in%201959%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Rossmoor%2C%20California.%20The%20model%20spread%20rapidly.%20By%201970%20there%20were%2010%2C000%20HOAs%20nationwide.%20By%202023%20there%20were%20some%20365%2C000%2C%20with%20more%20than%2075%20million%20Americans%20residing%20within%20their%20territory.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20understand%20why%20the%20HOA-ification%20of%20America%20is%20so%20pernicious%2C%20we%20must%20first%20understand%20what%20made%20HOAs%20so%20appealing%20in%20the%20first%20place.%20In%20his%20book%20%26quot%3BCrack-Up%20Capitalism%2C%26quot%3B%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethe%20historian%20Quinn%20Slobodian%20writes%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsilverleaf-village-scottsdale-arizona-expensive-neighborhood-photos-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egated%20communities%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20which%20are%20invariably%20managed%20by%20HOAs%20%E2%80%94%20represent%20a%20form%20of%20%26quot%3Bsoft%20secession%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20effort%20to%20create%20%26quot%3Balternative%20political%20arrangements%20at%20a%20small%20scale.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20form%20of%20%26quot%3Bsoft%20secession%26quot%3B%20has%20proved%20appealing%20to%20some%20prominent%20libertarian%20intellectuals.%20You%20might%20find%20it%20counterintuitive%20that%20minimal-government%20types%20would%20embrace%20a%20type%20of%20government%20that%20allows%20busybodies%20to%20regulate%20the%20color%20of%20their%20next-door%20neighbors'%20homes.%20But%20as%20Slobodian%20shows%2C%20more%20than%20a%20few%20prominent%20market%20fundamentalists%20have%20been%20drawn%20to%20the%20notion%20of%20a%20private-sector%20substitute%20for%20local%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConsider%20one%20of%20the%20characters%20in%20Slobodian's%20book%3A%20Gordon%20Tullock%2C%20an%20economist%20and%20public-choice%20theorist%20who%20spent%20much%20of%20his%20career%20at%20George%20Mason%20University.%20Tullock%20devoted%20an%20entire%20chapter%20of%20his%20book%20%26quot%3BThe%20New%20Federalist%26quot%3B%20to%20describing%20the%20HOA%20of%20Arizona's%20Sunshine%20Mountain%20Ridge%2C%20a%20community%20of%20250%20houses%20he%20then%20called%20home.%20In%20Tullock's%20telling%2C%20in%20exchange%20for%20an%20annual%20fee%20and%20residents'%20adherence%20to%20community%20rules%2C%20the%20HOA%20paid%20for%20road%20maintenance%2C%20private%20fire%20protection%2C%20landscaping%2C%20trash%20collection%2C%20and%20private%20security%20to%20supplement%20the%20protection%20offered%20by%20the%20Pima%20County%20sheriff.%20The%20association%20also%20provided%20its%20residents%20with%20%26quot%3Bthe%20usual%20privileges%20of%20a%20citizen%20in%20any%20free%20state%2C%26quot%3B%20Tullock%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Sunshine%20Mountain%20Ridge%20resident%20%26quot%3Bcan%20complain%20to%20the%20board%2C%20either%20by%20going%20to%20the%20regular%20meetings%20of%20the%20citizens%20of%20this%20little%20community%20or%20circulating%20petitions%2C%20run%20for%20office%2C%20or%20organize%20other%20people%20to%20run%20for%20office%20as%20a%20sort%20of%20party%2C%26quot%3B%20Tullock%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETullock%20praised%20the%20resulting%20quality%20of%20life%3A%20Sunshine%20Mountain%20Ridge%2C%20he%20wrote%2C%20is%20beautiful%2C%20provides%20high-quality%20services%20to%20its%20residents%2C%20and%20wields%20outsize%20political%20power%20in%20the%20county%20government.%20He%20also%20celebrated%20the%20neighborhood's%20homogeneity%3A%20%26quot%3BIt%20seems%20that%20people%2C%20on%20the%20whole%2C%20like%20living%20with%20other%20people%20who%20are%20similar%20to%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20Sunshine%20Mountain%20Ridge%20was%20mostly%20home%20to%20people%20like%20Tullock%2C%20that%20was%20%26quot%3Bemphatically%20not%20true%26quot%3B%20of%20surrounding%20areas%20%26quot%3Bwhere%20almost%201%2F3%20of%20the%20population%20is%20Mexican%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%20Given%20that%20part%20of%20the%20HOA%20model's%20appeal%20is%20its%20success%20in%20maintaining%20residential%20segregation%2C%20it's%20not%20entirely%20surprising%20that%20the%20HOA%20boom%20took%20off%20in%20the%20years%20following%20the%20fall%20of%20Jim%20Crow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20explosive%20growth%20was%20driven%20at%20least%20in%20part%20by%20market%20demand%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fscottsdale-vs-paradise-valley-phoenix-suburbs-compared-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efor%20the%20sort%20of%20exclusivity%3C%2Fa%3E%20Tullock%20lauded.%20A%202019%20study%20by%20the%20economists%20Wyatt%20Clarke%20and%20Matthew%20Freedman%20found%20that%20HOA%20home%20prices%20were%2C%20on%20average%2C%20higher%20than%20non-HOA%20home%20prices%20in%20the%20surrounding%20area%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20this%20%26quot%3BHOA%20premium%26quot%3B%20was%20strongly%20correlated%20with%20the%20size%20of%20an%20area's%20Black%20population%20as%20of%201960.%20The%20more%20Black%20residents%20a%20region%20had%20in%20the%20last%20decade%20of%20legalized%2C%20explicit%20racial%20segregation%2C%20the%20larger%20the%20gap%20between%20non-HOA%20home%20prices%20and%20HOA%20home%20prices.%20One%20can%20surmise%20that%20HOAs%20in%20these%20areas%20tend%20to%20be%20more%20exclusive%20in%20part%20because%20they%20were%20designed%20to%20exclude.%20Readers%20will%20not%20be%20shocked%20to%20learn%20that%20Clarke%20and%20Freedman%20also%20found%20that%20HOA%20residents%20were%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20white%20or%20Asian%20than%20non-HOA%20residents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%26quot%3Bsecession%20of%20the%20successful%26quot%3B%20into%20HOAs%2C%20as%20the%20former%20US%20labor%20secretary%20Robert%20Reich%20once%20put%20it%2C%20has%20consequences%20for%20everyone%20else.%20The%20legal%20scholar%20Sheryll%20Cashin%20has%20argued%20that%20HOAs%20erode%20the%20social%20contract%20and%20encourage%20residents%20to%20think%20of%20themselves%20as%20property%20owners%20first%20and%20citizens%20second.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20more%20and%20more%20citizens%20separate%20themselves%20into%20homogeneous%20private%20communities%2C%20their%20ties%20to%20the%20larger%20polity%20will%20become%20attenuated%20and%20they%20will%20increasingly%20resist%20governmental%20efforts%20to%20address%20problems%20that%20they%20do%20not%20perceive%20as%20'theirs'%2C%26quot%3B%20Cashin%20wrote%20in%202001.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20as%20Cashin%20noted%2C%20HOA%20members%20may%20be%20particularly%20hostile%20to%20public%20taxation%2C%20especially%20local%20property%20taxes.%20After%20all%2C%20they%20already%20pay%20HOA%20dues%20that%20fund%20private%20infrastructure%20in%20their%20communities%3B%20why%20pay%20again%20to%20subsidize%20public%20infrastructure%20outside%20the%20neighborhood%3F%20(Cashin%20observed%20that%20several%20states%2C%20including%20New%20Jersey%20and%20Texas%2C%20had%20laws%20allowing%20HOA%20residents%20to%20subtract%20the%20cost%20of%20privately%20provided%20infrastructure%20from%20their%20taxes.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20HOAs%20can%20and%20do%20use%20their%20political%20influence%20and%20land-use%20bylaws%20to%20prevent%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-housing-affordability-home-shortage-market-construction-population-cities-zillow-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econstruction%20of%20multifamily%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20low-cost%20housing%20in%20the%20territories%20they%20govern%20and%20the%20periphery.%20America%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhomes-real-estate-how-to-fix-housing-crisis-factors-construction-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eneeds%20millions%20of%20homes%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20meet%20demand%20and%20ease%20the%20upward%20pressure%20on%20housing%20costs%2C%20but%20many%20HOAs%20have%20rules%20to%20prevent%20building%20even%20small%20additions%2C%20such%20as%20accessory%20dwelling%20units%20%E2%80%94%20much%20less%20large%20developments%20like%20apartments.%20It's%20difficult%20to%20estimate%20just%20how%20much%20homebuilding%20HOAs%20have%20thwarted%20in%20supply-constrained%20areas.%20But%20one%20thing%20is%20certain%3A%20By%20acting%20as%20a%20bulwark%20against%20new%20housing%20supply%2C%20NIMBY%20HOAs%20contribute%20to%20the%20housing%20crisis%20and%20make%20inequality%20worse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20for%20the%20HOA%20members%2C%20the%20supposed%20upsides%20of%20these%20associations%20can%20become%20a%20burden.%20Many%20Americans%20who%20live%20in%20HOAs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2023%2F10%2F31%2Fwhat-the-rise-of-homeowners-associations-means-for-americans.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eface%20steep%20fines%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20trivial%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsoctv.com%2Fnews%2Flocal%2Fhomeowner-facing-more-than-12000-fines-lien-sues-hoa-has-been-winning%2FYPU2JSGJWJBXDCQZIDFMZPDPVY%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einfractions%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20some%20have%20even%20faced%20eviction%20for%20seemingly%20minor%20violations%20of%20neighborhood%20codes.%20For%20instance%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcypress-texas-hoa-sues-homeowners-for-feeding-ducks-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20couple%20in%20Texas%20was%20sued%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202022%20by%20their%20HOA%20for%20%24250%2C000%20%E2%80%94%20for%20the%20crime%20of%20feeding%20ducks%20near%20their%20home.%20These%20are%20the%20kinds%20of%20abuses%20that%20Florida's%20new%20law%20is%20intended%20to%20halt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Florida's%20reforms%20will%20do%20little%20to%20address%20the%20structural%20problems%20with%20the%20HOA%20model.%20Little%20wonder%2C%20since%20Florida's%20far-right%20state%20government%20is%20an%20indirect%20beneficiary%20of%20those%20harms%3B%20the%20state's%20evolution%20into%20an%20HOA%20republic%20has%20likely%20been%20a%20factor%20in%20its%20transformation%20from%20a%20swing%20state%20into%20a%20laboratory%20for%20reaction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20growth%20of%20these%20little%20private%20governments%20has%20helped%20entrench%20segregation%20along%20racial%20and%20class%20lines%2C%20fueled%20the%20atomization%20of%20American%20public%20life%2C%20and%20worsened%20the%20material%20quality%20of%20life%20for%20millions%20of%20Americans.%20That's%20a%20far%20more%20pressing%20issue%20than%20HOA%20standards%20around%20lawn%20care.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fned-resnikoff%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3ENed%20Resnikoff%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20the%20policy%20director%20of%20California%20YIMBY%20and%20co-leader%20of%20the%20Metropolitan%20Abundance%20Project.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fabolish-hoas-homeowner-associations-housing-market-real-estate-costs-2024-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1720430822000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F667ed9bbd1c84a0eaca8c580%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fabolish-hoas-homeowner-associations-housing-market-real-estate-costs-2024-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Florida%20is%20trying%20to%20crush%20the%20local%20dictators%20ruining%20homeowners'%20lives.%20The%20rest%20of%20America%20should%20follow%20suit.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Ned%20Resnikoff)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fabolish-hoas-homeowner-associations-housing-market-real-estate-costs-2024-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%2225%20Years%20Later%2C%20Family%20Still%20Seeks%20Justice%20For%20Kargil%20War%20Hero's%20Torture%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ETwenty-five%20years%20ago%2C%20Captain%20Saurabh%20Kalia%20became%20the%20first%20Indian%20army%20officer%20to%20be%20killed%20in%20the%20Kargil%20War.%20He%20was%20captured%20by%20Pakistani%20forces%20along%20with%20five%20other%20soldiers%20and%20subjected%20to%20brutal%20torture%20for%2022%20days%20before%20being%20killed.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnIn%20an%20interview%2C%20Captain%20Kalia's%20parents%2C%20Dr%20Narendra%20Kalia%20and%20Mrs%20Vijaya%20Kalia%2C%20recalled%20the%20pain%20and%20devastation%20they%20felt%20upon%20learning%20of%20their%20son's%20death.%20However%2C%20the%20outpouring%20of%20love%20and%20respect%20from%20people%20across%20the%20country%20has%20given%20them%20some%20comfort%2C%20they%20say.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cstrong%3EWho%20was%20Captain%20Saurabh%20Kalia%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnCaptain%20Saurabh%20Kalia%20was%20born%20on%20January%2029%2C%201976%2C%20in%20Amritsar%2C%20and%20grew%20up%20in%20Palampur%2C%20Himachal%20Pradesh.%20He%20completed%20his%20schooling%20at%20DAV%20Public%20School%20and%20higher%20secondary%20education%20at%20Kendriya%20Vidyalaya%20in%20Palampur.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnDriven%20by%20a%20desire%20to%20serve%20the%20country%2C%20Saurabh%20Kalia%20joined%20the%20army%20through%20the%20CDSR%20and%20was%20commissioned%20as%20an%20officer%20in%204%20Jat%20on%20December%2012%2C%201998.%20He%20was%20deployed%20to%20Kargil%2C%20where%20he%20managed%20general%20duties%20at%20the%20Baharng%20Complex%20at%20an%20altitude%20of%20over%2017%2C000%20feet%20and%20monitored%20infiltrations%20in%20the%20Kaksar%20sub-sector.%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20happened%20to%20Captain%20Saurabh%20Kalia%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnOn%20May%2015%2C%201999%2C%20Captain%20Kalia%20and%20five%20soldiers%20were%20on%20a%20routine%20patrol%20when%20they%20were%20ambushed%20and%20captured%20alive%20by%20Pakistani%20forces.%20They%20were%20held%20captive%20for%2022%20days%20and%20tortured%20to%20death.%20Their%20bodies%20were%20returned%20by%20the%20Pakistani%20army%20on%20June%209%2C%201999.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnCaptain%20Saurabh%20Kalia's%20mother%20recalls%20learning%20of%20her%20son's%20death%20through%20a%20newspaper%20article%2C%20a%20pain%20that%20lingers%2025%20years%20later.%20They%20went%20to%20confirm%20the%20news%20at%20the%20Palampur%20army%20office%20and%20were%20met%20with%20the%20stark%20reality%20that%20%26quot%3Bno%20news%20is%20good%20news%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20military.%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnThough%20time%20has%20somewhat%20eased%20her%20grief%2C%20the%20inhumane%20torture%20inflicted%20on%20Saurabh%20and%20his%20comrades%20continues%20to%20haunt%20her.%20Captain%20Saurabh%20Kalia's%20father%20remembers%20his%20son%20as%20a%20calm%20and%20thoughtful%20person.%20He%20has%20been%20fighting%20for%20justice%20for%20his%20son's%20mistreatment%2C%20but%20the%20government%20has%20not%20taken%20action%20as%20of%20yet.%20He%20even%20took%20the%20case%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20but%20unfortunately%2C%20there%20has%20been%20no%20progress%20since%20the%20Covid%20pandemic.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnOn%20the%2025th%20anniversary%20of%20the%20Kargil%20War%2C%20Captain%20Kargil's%20father%20appealed%20to%20all%20citizens%20to%20show%20respect%20and%20gratitude%20to%20soldiers%20who%20served%20the%20nation%20in%20extreme%20conditions%2C%20from%20-50%20to%20%2B50%20degrees%20Celsius.%20He%20also%20said%20that%20Pakistan%20can't%20be%20trusted%2C%20like%20a%20dog's%20tail%20that%20will%20never%20straighten.%E2%80%9D%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cstrong%3EKargil%20War%C2%A0(1999)%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnIndia%20and%20Pakistan%20were%20involved%20in%20a%20war%20from%20May%20to%20July%201999%20in%20the%20Kargil%20district%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%20The%20conflict%20began%20when%20Pakistani%20troops%20infiltrated%20Indian%20positions%20across%20the%20Line%20of%20Control%20(LoC).%20In%20response%2C%20India%20launched%20Operations%20Vijay%20and%20Safed%20Sagar%20to%20reclaim%20the%20occupied%20territories.%20The%20war%20included%20significant%20battles%2C%20such%20as%20the%20recapture%20of%20Tiger%20Hill%20and%20Tololing.%20Ultimately%2C%20India%20won%2C%20forcing%20Pakistan%20to%20withdraw%20its%20troops.%20The%20conflict%20ended%20with%20a%20return%20to%20the%20pre-conflict%20status%20quo.%20India%20suffered%20527%20casualties%20during%20the%20war.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22publis