g%20with%20a%20steel%20dagger%2C%20and%20looking%20across%20a%20table%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66881fd91f0c1cd6d731df07%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETom%20Glynn-Carney%20as%20Aegon%20II%20Targaryen%20in%20%26quot%3BHouse%20of%20the%20Dragon%26quot%3B%20season%20two.%3Cp%3EOllie%20Upton%2FHBO%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223b62c55b-04b0-49ad-87b4-205f24b97e1c%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAegon%20and%20Sunfyre%20do%20eventually%20die%2C%20though%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELater%20in%20the%20war%2C%20a%20small%20force%20loyal%20to%20Rhaenyra%20takes%20back%20Rook's%20Rest%20and%20attempts%20to%20kill%20Sunfyre.%20They%20do%20not%20succeed%2C%20but%20shortly%20after%2C%20Sunfyre%20is%20nowhere%20to%20be%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Rhaenyra%20takes%20King's%20Landing%2C%20Aegon%20is%20gone%2C%20as%20are%20his%20remaining%20children%2C%20Jaehara%20and%20Maelor.%20According%20to%20one%20historical%20record%20referenced%20in%20%26quot%3BFire%20and%20Blood%2C%26quot%3B%20Larys%20Strong%20smuggled%20them%20out%20of%20the%20city%2C%20setting%20Aegon%20aboard%20a%20fishing%20boat%20bound%20for%20Dragonstone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAegon%20hides%20there%20until%20Sunfyre%20makes%20his%20way%20to%20the%20island%20after%20disappearing%20for%20half%20a%20year%2C%20his%20wing%20healed%20enough%20to%20barely%20allow%20him%20to%20fly.%20The%20two%20begin%20to%20fly%20together%20again%2C%20and%20eventually%2C%20a%20force%20loyal%20to%20Aegon%20takes%20over%20the%20island.%20Aegon%20and%20Sunfyre%20are%20forced%20to%20fight%20Baela%2C%20Daemon%20and%20Laena's%20daughter%2C%20and%20her%20dragon%20Moondancer.%20The%20clash%20leaves%20Moondancer%20dead%2C%20Sunfyre%20unable%20to%20fly%20again%2C%20Aegon%20with%20two%20broken%20legs%20after%20jumping%20out%20of%20the%20saddle%2C%20and%20Baela%20taken%20prisoner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it%20also%20leaves%20Aegon%20in%20possession%20of%20Dragonstone.%20When%20Rhaenyra%20arrives%2C%20he%20promptly%20feeds%20her%20to%20his%20dragon%2C%20Sunfyre.%20Shortly%20after%2C%20Sunfyre%20dies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAegon%20returns%20to%20King's%20Landing%20after%20his%20mother%20Alicent%20strikes%20an%20accord%20with%20Lord%20Corlys%20Velaryon%2C%20lifting%20the%20Velaryon%20blockade%20that%20prevented%20his%20return.%20There%2C%20he%20sits%20not%20on%20the%20Iron%20Throne%20but%20on%20a%20seat%20at%20its%20steps%2C%20as%20a%20result%20of%20his%20broken%20legs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20King%20then%20seeks%20revenge%20on%20those%20who%20acted%20against%20him%20during%20the%20war%2C%20forcing%20lords%20in%20the%20surrounding%20crownlands%20to%20submit%20to%20him.%20But%20while%20Aegon's%20council%20frets%20over%20how%20to%20quell%20the%20coming%20rebellion%20from%20across%20Westeros%2C%20Aegon%20is%20preoccupied%20with%20matters%20of%20succession%3A%20he%20wishes%20to%20marry%20Lady%20Cassandra%20Baratheon%20and%20produce%20new%20heirs.%20(In%20the%20book%2C%20Aegon's%20sister-wife%20Helaena%20dies%20by%20suicide%20after%20the%20death%20of%20their%20son%20Maelor.)%20Similarly%2C%20he%20wants%20to%20prevent%20the%20betrothal%20of%20his%20daughter%20Jaehaera%20to%20Rhaenyra's%20son%2C%20Aegon%20the%20younger%2C%20so%20as%20to%20finish%20off%20Rhaenyra's%20bloodline.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEventually%2C%20with%20armies%20encroaching%20on%20King's%20Landing%2C%20Aegon%20is%20poisoned%20while%20being%20carried%20in%20his%20litter%20to%20the%20Sept%20via%20a%20cup%20of%20laced%20wine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%26quot%3BHouse%20of%20the%20Dragon%26quot%3B%20season%20two%20airs%20Sundays%20at%209%20p.m.%20ET%20on%20HBO%20and%20is%20streaming%20on%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3Dfed657e5d456898628c785351016f7b12b4d269a5d17af0f15435159aef229d0%26postID%3D6685c2e5cbc59e61ceb693b6%26postSlug%3Dis-aegon-dead-alive-house-of-the-dragon-book-2024-